  "commentary": "With SPX at 7040 trading between the max negative gamma at 7015 and max positive gamma at 7050, dealers are likely covering short deltas from the recent -1.3% move, providing buying support here. The PIN regime with massive positive GEX walls at 7050 (+12.2B) and 7100 (+11.2B) suggests dealers will aggressively sell any push higher, while the proximity to max negative gamma at 7015 means accelerated buying if we break lower. Watch 7015 as the key support level where dealer buying intensifies and 7050 as the primary resistance where dealer selling kicks in.\n\nBottom line: expect choppy trading range between 7015-7050 with limited upside.",
